features: Performance: AGI AI218 NVMe M.2 Gen 3x4, SLC caching PCIe SSD with 3D TLC NAND offers great speed and performance. With read speeds of up to 3500MB/s and write speeds of up to 3100MB/s, this SSD can handle the demanding workloads with ease.

GENeration : The Gen 3x4 interface is capable of delivering exceptional read/write speeds, with theoretical transfer rates of up to 4 GB/s, which means you can transfer large files and load applications in seconds.

Lightning-fast processing: Equipped with DRAM and SLC caching, the AI218 SSD delivers lightning-fast read and write speeds for faster boot times, application loading, and file transfers. DRAM and SLC caching work together also reduce write amplification, which helps to extend the life of the SSD and ensure long-term reliability.

Faster cooling: AGI AI218 provides graphene heat sink, offering faster heat dissipation, providing a reliable and long-lasting cooling solution for your SSD, keeping your SSD running at optimal temperatures.

Reliable and stable performance: The combination of S.M.A.R.T, TRIM Command, APM, NCQ, and ECC engine in AI218 provides reliable and stable performance, reducing the risk of data loss or corruption and ensuring your data remains safe and secure, knowing that your SSD is equipped with advanced features to protect your data.
body.description: The AGI AI218 solid state drive with DRAM acceleration featuring revolutionary PCIe Gen 3 x 4 interface can run at a speed 5 times faster than SATAIII SSD. A huge leap in performance. NVME 1.3 transmission greatly accelerates your gaming experience Featuring LDPC ECC technology for reliability. TRIM and NCQ technology optimize the performance throughout the whole life cycle. NANDXtend three-level error correction algorithm can decode in parallel and correct errors with precision and at high speed. Together, these technologies extend the P/E cycle performance of 3D NAND, prolonging the SSD's lifespan and ensuring data integrity.
